Scanning Tools & Concepts :-

Network Scanning Concepts

Finding active hosts, open ports, running services, operating systems, 
and vulnerabilities within a network is known as network scanning.

It is a critical phase of:
• Ethical Hacking
• Penetration Testing
• Vulnerability Assessment 
• Network Administration 

• Objectives of Network Scanning

1. Discover live hosts.
2. Identify open ports.
3. Detect running services.
4. Determine operating systems.
5. Identify network topology.
6. Discover security weaknesses. 

• Network Scanning Phases :-

Target Identification
         ↓
   Host Discovery
         ↓
   Port Discovery
         ↓
 Service Enumeration
         ↓
  OS Fingerprinting
         ↓
Vulnerability Assessment

Types of Scanning :-

Type                                 |      Purpose
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Network Scanning                     |      Discover devices
Port Scanning                        |      Find open ports
Vulnerability Scanning               |      Identify weaknesses
Service Scanning                     |      Identify services
OS Scanning                          |      Identify operating systems
